# Your project

Replace this heading with your repository name and add a one-line description.

This repository is an [Eval System](https://github.com/zoto-agents/zoto-agents) host for static pytest and LLM evals against Cursor primitives. Customize this file for your team; it is stamped at repo root on first init/create when missing and is never overwritten if it already exists.

## Cursor primitives

| Primitive | Location | Notes |
|-----------|----------|-------|
| **Skill** | `.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` | Workflow guidance with trigger phrases in frontmatter |
| **Rule** | `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Style and scope constraints (`globs`, `alwaysApply`) |
| **Command** | `.cursor/commands/*.md` | User-invoked slash commands |
| **Agent** | `.cursor/agents/*.md` | Focused subagent definitions |
| **Hook** | `.cursor/hooks.json` + `.cursor/hooks/*` | Event-driven policy scripts |
| **AGENTS.md** | repo root | Repo-wide agent instructions ([AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)) |

### Cross-cutting best practices

1. **Frontmatter is the contract** — `name` + `description` (and for rules: `globs` / `alwaysApply`) drive discovery. Write descriptions in third person with explicit trigger phrases.
2. **One job per primitive** — Skills teach workflows; rules constrain style; commands orchestrate user-invoked flows; agents run focused sub-tasks; hooks enforce policy at events.
3. **Commands own `askQuestion`** — Subagents and skills should not prompt directly; return structured `needs_user_input` and let the command resume the Task.
4. **Keep tokens cheap** — Under ~50 lines for rules; skills should assume the model is capable and only add domain-specific facts.
5. **Executable hooks** — `chmod +x` hook scripts; verify `jq`/`node` exist in the hook environment; prefer `failClosed: true` for security gates.

### Typical layout

```
your-repo/
├── AGENTS.md
├── README.md
├── .cursor/
│   ├── rules/
│   ├── skills/
│   ├── commands/
│   ├── agents/
│   ├── hooks.json
│   └── hooks/
└── .zoto/eval-system/    # Eval System config + manifest
```

## Eval System

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `pnpm run eval` | Static pytest suite |
| `pnpm run eval:full` | Static + LLM (`CURSOR_API_KEY` in `.env`) |
| `pnpm run eval:update:check` | Drift check (exit 2 on critical drift) |

Slash commands (requires the zoto-eval-system plugin): `/z-eval-init`, `/z-eval-create`, `/z-eval-execute`, `/z-eval-help`, and related `/z-eval-*` commands.

Run artefacts: `evals/_runs/<timestamp>/` (`report.yml`, `static.yml`, `llm.yml`).
